\033[1m\033[36mff - Fast command generator with AI\033[0m

\033[1mDESCRIPTION:\033[0m
  Uses OpenRouter AI to generate command line commands from natural language.
  The generated command is pre-filled in your terminal input for editing.

\033[1mUSAGE:\033[0m
  ff <description of what you want to do>

\033[1mEXAMPLES:\033[0m
  ff list all python files recursively
  ff find files modified in the last 24 hours
  ff compress all images in current directory
  ff show disk usage sorted by size
  ff kill process using port 3000

\033[1mFEATURES:\033[0m
  • Natural language to command translation
  • Context-aware (knows current directory)
  • Pre-fills command in terminal (zsh: directly, bash: via history)
  • Edit before executing by pressing Enter
  • Uses OpenRouter API with configurable model

\033[1mCONFIGURATION:\033[0m
  Requires OpenRouter API key in config.json:
    {
      "openrouter": {
        "apiKey": "your-api-key-here"
      }
    }

  Get your API key at: https://openrouter.ai/keys

\033[1mOPTIONS:\033[0m
  -h, --help    Show this help message

\033[1mNOTES:\033[0m
  • In zsh: Command appears directly in input buffer
  • In bash: Command saved to history, press ↑ to use
  • Edit the command as needed before pressing Enter
  • Model can be configured in config.json